        # Implementation Plan: M6b Process UX And Canary

## Overview
Wire trusted-local process runtime state into the video editor host surfaces without giving processes timeline mutation rights. The codebase already has most of the runtime contracts: `ProcessManager`, process descriptors, planner blockers, `process.result.attach` creation/projection, and existing jsdom/browser canary patterns. The missing work is host ownership and visibility: expose a provider-scoped `processManager`, add the PropertiesPanel process dashboard, add guarded `start-process` planner actions, and pass `ProcessResultAttachRecord` evidence into planner/material/export paths before returned refs are consumed.

This scope is a bridge, not a contradiction, against the North Star: it advances trusted process observability, route-scoped repair, and durable returned-ref provenance while explicitly keeping process runtime and output-format sidecars outside the V1 composition SDK and preserving the no-direct-timeline-mutation constraint. No anchor conflict identified.

