3. process-result-attach-evidence-wiring: Trace the data flow from ProcessManager.execute() → ProcessRoundtripResult → createProcessResultAttachRecord() → projectProcessResultContracts() into the planner, export guard, and material-artifact consumers. Identify the exact interception point where process.result.attach evidence (processRef, operationId, taskId, status, returnedMaterialRefs, diagnostics, provenance) must be visible before downstream consumers read returned refs and timeline-facing patches consume results. Determine whether this requires a new planner diagnostic, a new material status projection, or an enrichment of existing RenderMaterial.provenance. The contract is already built (processResultAttach.ts); the gap is making it inspectable in the UI/planner before consumption.
